				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				i'm going to make a desperate attempt to stop the bs posting on this thread.  i didn't bother to count the total amount of time i spent camping pyzjn over the last 6 months, but i can tell you it was a lot.  i started camping the stone at about level 27, many of my friends surpassed me by 20 levels or more as i camped this stone, to give you a vague idea of how much time i spent at it.  i have recieved the gbs twice, one of which i blatently ks'd from someone.  i felt guilty because both of us being hard core pyzjn campers, i talked with him frequently and had seen him camping the stone even more religiously than i.  i handed over the stone to him.  now that i have stated my resume' *smile* i'll move on to the facts that can't be argued about this spawn, and perhaps provide a bit of logic.  i'd wager that noone, including myself, *other than game designers* knows how many true spawn points that pyzjn has.  every time i think i have a good idea of how many she has, up pops another one.  out of the 14 times i have killed pyzjn, and seeing her an additional 3-4, i have only seen her actually spawn one time.  not once have i seen her pop at the ruins, doesn't mean it doesn't happen though.  it is my belief that all of her spawns walk to the ruins and sit in her usual place, (inside the ruins, towards bb side), and she turns to face SG, or what i believe to be made to look as if she is looking in varsoon's direction, who might be triggered by her standing here.  after all who in their right mind would let pyzjn sit there to find out.  everytime i have killed her she was walking to this point, however i never let her get there if i saw her.  now about tovax, i dont believe he has any chance of being a place holder.  Mainly because he doesn't hold her place, just using simple logic here.  varsoon i believed to have nothing to do with her spawn because i didn't believe he held her place either, and he usually doesn't.  however i did log on one time and see him standing in pyzjn's spot (human form)  its very possible that he spawned  and ran over there to stab a newbie to death, but just seeing him there is enough to suggest he might have something to do with her place, while tovax gives no evidence what so ever.  90% of the time u cant even track tovax from the ruins.  i do however know a way to test tovax thoroughly.  i believe he only has one spawn point, which is right behind the guard tower near wk zone.  park your pet there, then run back to the ruins *sit* and watch.  if you are kos to tovax, even if he is way green, he should attack your pet if you are sitting.  if your pet is like my pet tovax will be dead in a couple seconds.  i've seen necro's park their pet at raiders in nk and sit afk out of site of the raiders for free faction.   they all jump the pet which slaughters them.    now on to the spawns that are definently her place holders.  if you see a grizly bear anywhere near the ruins, i'll bet you $20 its a ph.  it only spawns during the day, and everytime i have seen it (100 or more, way more common that pyz) it has walked to her point and turned to look at sg, just as pyzjn does.  sometimes the second it turns to face sg, it despawns.  most of the time it will sit there and not move again (like pyzjn) until it is killed, maybe it will despawn evetually but i have watched it for as much as 15 mins before a newbie killed it.  also, if you see a *giant* rat my $20 bet is also valid here, everytime i have seen it, (much less common than the grizly) it has shared the same habbits, ie not moving until killed, and facing sg.  both grizlys and giant rats can be found elseware in the zone, but never within sight of the ruins.  large rats are very common near the ruins, so don't confuse them with giant rat.  there are many other common daytime spawns that walk to pyzjn's spot, but are much harder to spot right off because others of their type are all around the ruins.  The ones i have seen, and there may be others are a fire beetle, gray wolf, and large rat (cant remember seeing any other)  i can tell you specifically that it is never a snake, or any type of bat.  sometimes you will see them sit in her spot, but they do not turn to sg, and a few seconds later, they will begin walking away.  now on to the nighttime spawns.  never at night have i seen a grizzly go to the ruins, or any of the other daytime spawns except the giant rat that i saw there at midnight once.  this means u shouldnt see a gray wolf, fire beetle, grizzly and most likely not the giant rat at night either.  (im talking about the pyzjn spawn here, i know they exist elseware in the zone at night) the night time ph's i have seen have been a skeleton, a putrid skeleton, and a dread corpse.  they, like the others are very distinctive by walking to pyzjn's spot, turning to face sg, and not moving again until aggro.  almost always if u see a dread or putrid coming from over the hill, they are a ph, not always but almost.  one distinctive thing i have noticed about the skeleton ph is that it has the same resistances of a dread corpse or putrid skeleton which is almost an infinite resistance to poison, disease, and ice spells.  i am a shaman so that is about all i have, i have a 6dmg burst of flame nuke that they do not resist, which makes me believe that it is more cold/poison/disease resistance, rather than just an overall magical resistance (that and i've seen other classes blast them)  all other skeletons i can easily nuke to death with my ice dd.  as you can probably tell by the size of this post, which i apologize for, is just about everything i *know* about this spawn.  it is not a collection of information from these posts, however much of it i have seen here, but not all in the same post.  none of this information is likely to help you to find pyzjn any faster, or make the camp any easier.  what this information can do is help you to camp pyzjn without a head full of crap that u aquired on this thread.  the reason i am posting is because i want to expand on these known facts.  i would love it if people would take this information and make it useful, such as trying to track down the origin of these ph's during the day while you are waiting for nightfall.  by now you should know pyzjn is nighttime only, even though there are those that say they have seen her in the daytime.  this zone shows the same pattern as the undead in kithicor forest.  there are distinct day and nighttime spawns.  at 8pm, nighttime spawns will start spawning, at 6am, nighttime spawns will stop spawning, and despawn anywhere between 6am and 8am.  this means, pyzjn could be alive until 7am, but will not spawn after 5am.  what if these spawn points spawn in order? and during your camp you could move from one point to another eliminated the ph's as they spawn.  what if there is a spawn point that spawns 3 times for every one of the others?  this stuff we will never know until we track down the exact spawn points.  shes not so random that any mob in the zone can be her ph, i refuse to believe that, there is no evidence of it.  i also don't believe that she can have a ph that doesn't share her place, i know its possible, and have seen it elseware in the game, such as varsoon the undying spawn being triggered by killing the human version.  i'll explain why this is almost impossible.  if it could be any spawn that triggered her spawn, or even a ph, pyzjn would be a heck of a lot more common.  there would be newbies all over the zone helping pyzjn spawn by killing rats, bats, beetles and the like.  if it was an npc, eventually it would become known just as all other triggered spawns, because pyzjn would keep popping as u killed that npc.  another thing about the spawn...   i have never seen 2 ph's at the ruins at the same time, which most likely means that only 1 of these potential pyzjn spawns can be up at one time.  i believe that this potential spawn is timed, approx 4 game hours.  yet it wont take you long to see that if you sit at the ruins you will not see a ph every 4 game hours or even close to that.  this could be because they got killed before they became within sight, that they were trained to a guard, or what i believe might be the case is that they have many different walking patterns.  what i mean is, some of the spawns will head directly to the ruins, while others might make a stop at the local tree for a few seconds and walk around elseware before ending up at the ruins.  we'll never know for sure though until we know exactly where all the spawn points are.  how do i find out where they spawn?  this is the hard part.  u can keep close watch for the potential spawns coming from a distance, if it turns out to be a ph, run to the furthest distance that you noticed it coming (i.e. maybe u saw it pass very close to a tree that u can see in the distance) and wait there for that spawn to come again, and try to trace it back further.  another way would be to know what the potential ph's are (i mentioned them earlier) and note the /loc of where u first saw them, and then follow and see if they truely end up in pyzjn's spot.  this is not easy stuff but might give you something to do while you wait for night time to camp pyzjn.  to people that know this spawn as well as i do, and want to clear up the crap on this thread also, please post here and back me up.  also if you have anything to add please do so, i will be looking back and trying any new suggestions, and pointing out what i already know is crap so as to hopefully keep people steered in the right direction to figuring this spawn out.  disclaimer: lots of this information cannot be proved beyond a shadow of a doubt, just use your head, thats what i've done, and this is all the *most likely* scenerio.  its very possible that some stinkin rat that never gets killed until it wanders past surefall guards or something every 4 hours or so triggers the spawn.  its just very unlikely.  keep that in mind please before u start throwing stones.  i would not be posting here if i had this spawn figured out.  i know what u all want here is someone to tell you exactly how to get a gbs in less than 30 mintues.  if such a thing is possible, this is what it is going to take to find out.  its not known by anyone that i know, whether this is possible or not, but i do believe that once we find these spawn points, we will at least know for sure whether it is possible to speed up this spawn consistantly or not.  it probably isn't, but at least we can end this everlasting thread of crapola. plz help.<BR>
<BR>
PyzjnSlayer (no its not my real character name, its actually my pets name heh heh)<BR>
shaman of the 45th winter<BR>
<BR>
(sorry this is so long)
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
